    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith extui enabled, `confirm` doesn't show anything until a key is pressed. This is particularly a problem when using `vim.pack`\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d004ed67-e401-41e7-a56e-beb780af04f1\n\nIn the video I am pressing a key to make it appear after waiting. Without pressing any keys, nothing happens\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._extui\").enable({})\n\nvim.fn.confirm(\"Hello\\nWorld\", \"&Yes\\n&No\")\n```\n\nUse this minimal init.lua\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWould expect it to show the confirmation without pressing any button first\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1564+g130ef73e39\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.0.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from source",
